post_text:
Keeping the Community Informed: COVID-19 Updates for Montezuma CSD

In an effort to keep students, staff, parents, and the entire community aware of how COVID-19 is impacting our district, we plan to share as much information as possible while protecting the privacy of those affected. Look to the COVID-19 page on the district website www.montezuma-schools.org daily for updates regarding the reports of positive cases for students and staff. Data will be updated daily on the days school is in session.

Individuals identified as close contacts per the Department of Public Health will be notified about positive COVID-19 cases in the district. Appropriate actions will be taken in the district to thoroughly clean, sanitize, and disinfect any impacted areas. Classes will continue as scheduled unless announced otherwise.

As we continue to work together during this time, we urge our staff and families to continue to wear face coverings when in public, social distance, cover coughs, and wash hands frequently to reduce the spread of this virus.

In our effort to keep everyone healthy, Montezuma CSD is following quarantine and isolation guidelines set by the CDC and Poweshiek County public health. Please be aware that beginning August 11th 2020, if your student comes in close contact (within 6ft for 15 mins or greater) with a positive COVID-19 individual, the 14 day quarantine will affect the model of learning for your student's start of the school year. Please contact Montezuma CSD administration to discuss your student's altered first days of school in the event that you come in close contact with a positive COVID-19 individual.

Thank you for your attention to this. We look forward to welcoming our students back to school on August 25th.

post_text:
Montezuma Families and Stakeholders-

Below you will find a summary of the Montezuma Community School District Return to Learn plan. It can be found on our website, or click on

https://drive.google.com/file/d/138pZoaWl4sNbHCQhkDREsr-yI_fMKDjh/view?usp=sharing

As you will see in this plan, the district plans to open school in a face to face setting with students and staff on August 25th. We are continuing to work with various district stakeholders to develop comprehensive safety protocols and procedures to ensure that everyone has a successful start to the school year. We are continuing to work on the details of certain parts of our day. In the next few weeks, we will be continually providing information to staff and community stakeholders. With all of this being said, we will continue to modify our plans as we work with local and state departments. If you have specific questions or concerns, please contact the Montezuma School office. As always, we thank you for your support as we work together through this process.

post_text:
After Graduation on Sunday, June 21 there will be a parade around town to honor our graduates. We are asking our families to limit the number of people attending, so we hope the parade will be a great way to congratulate our seniors. We also plan to live stream the event via our school FaceBook page and will have more details on this later in the week. Here is the reverse parade route. We believe this will take place at approximately 4:00 PM on Sunday. Please spread the word.

Head south out of the north lot, West on Irwin, back south on 3rd down to Liberty Street, east on Liberty to 4th Street, north on 4th and back towards the school. Kind of a reverse parade route that we normally do but this will give people the opportunity to park at the Presbyterian Church and Family Center, all around the square and on the side streets as well as in the south lot of the school.

post_text:
The Montezuma girls and boys basketball teams are scheduled to play Belle Plaine on Friday night. There is a chance of a winter storm so we are considering options to reschedule the game if necessary. Belle Plaine has a make-up game scheduled for Thursday night already so that is not an option. If the game is canceled Friday night, we are planning on playing Saturday if the road conditions are acceptable.

We will make updates on this website when they become available.

Thank you,
Montezuma Administration
